// The demo mod bundle. A mod is the SAME shape as the base game: a folder with a
// `*.bundle.ron` manifest listing its content files (paths relative to this
// folder) plus a `meta` self-description (name/description/author/version...,
// what the Mods menu and details panel show). This one has a single content file
// that both OVERRIDES a base section and ADDS a new scenario. It is listed in
// `assets/mods.catalog.ron`; enable it from the main-menu Mods section (or by
// adding its id to `EnabledMods`). `base` is an implicit dependency - mods do
// not declare it.
(
    content: ["mod.content.ron"],
    meta: (
        name: "Demo Mod",
        description: "Example mod: up-armors a hull section and adds an arena scenario.",
        author: "Nova Protocol",
        version: "1.0.0",
        dependencies: ["base"],
    ),
)
